For those who think there aren't enough seeders, please consider this: To be a seeder, you first must DL all 73 Gib of data in order to become eligible.  How many of us can afford to do this?  Sure...I'm a leech, but my share ratio is nearly 2 to 1.  I only plan to DL about a tenth of what is being offered but I'll gladly share twice whatever I'm able to DL.

When you're dealing with mega-sized torrents such as this, you can't expect the majority of downloaders to become seeders.  Most of us quite simply don't have the capacity to do that.

I will gladly share whatever is downloaded, but I'm not about to download ALL of a torrent, just so I can be labeled a seeder. 

The way I see it, if you upload more than you download, then you're a seeder.  

Seems like the original definition of 'seeder' worked great until some torrents grew to sizes too large to download in their entirety.

If I'm giving you twice what you're giving me, how can you can me a leech?
